step 1: open the killer coda
  https://killercoda.com/playgrounds/scenario/ubuntu
step 2 : update apt and install ngx serve
  sudo apt update 
  sudo apt install nginx 
step 3 : create a new directory name as you want
step 4 : clone any repository from
  https://github.com/topics/static-website?l=html&o=asc&s=stars
step 5 : copy the clone directory to /var/www/html
  cp -r /root/rahul/Personal-website/*   /var/www/html
step 6 : run the nginx server 
